By: IOL Motoring Staff Although not open to the general public, the Sema Show in Las Vegas prides itself on being the premier aftermarket show in the world, attracting over 100 000 industry leaders from around the world. The 2016 show was the usual feast of crazy hot rods, modified muscle cars and monster trucks, while the car manufacturers also got in on the action with a wild array of concept cars. Pictures: Newspress.  Like us on Facebook   Follow us on Twitter   Subscribe to our Newsletter 